      "safetyNotes": "Wear safety goggles throughout the demonstration. Teacher only handles the Bunsen burner, nichrome wire loops, and chemical solutions — students observe from their seats at a minimum distance of 1.5 metres. Solutions used: saturated sodium chloride, 0.1 M potassium permanganate, and 0.1 M copper sulphate — all low-hazard at these concentrations but must not be ingested. Copper sulphate is a mild irritant; teacher wears disposable gloves. Ensure the room is ventilated. A damp cloth and sand tray must be on the demonstration bench. Long hair must be tied back. No student approaches the flame without explicit teacher instruction."
